- Virtual Reality (VR) is an interactive computer-generated experience taking place within a simulated environment. VR games require specific hardware, such as head-mounted displays and motion controllers.
- Pros: They can provide incredible immersion through high fidelity environment and engagement of multiple senses. 
- Cons: The hardware required is expensive and not practical to carry around. Long use can cause nausea and eye strain.
- Suitable for: VR games are often used in medical and training fields.